						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the Kāmarasavalli-ammaṉ shrine in the Brahmapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sadāśivadēva-mahārāya Śaka 14(90): 1568 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The details of date <hi rend="italic">viz.,</hi> śaka 14(90), Vibhava, Siṁha, śu 10, Monday, Tiruvōṇam may be equated with 1568 A.D., August 2, Monday. However, the <hi rend="italic">nakshatra</hi> was Jyēshṭha.</p>						

						<p>This highly damaged inscription seems to record some gift for the śrībali offerings, lamps etc., to the deity Tiru Ayanīśurattu-nāyaṉar of Vaḻugūr probably by Śūrappa-nāyakkar, who is described as the agent <hi rend="italic">(karttar)</hi> of Kṛishṇappa-nāyakkar.</p>						

						</summary>
